the days you have left picture this you are working hard a single parent cautious yet you still live your children come first you want to go after all the dreams you've ever had chase them until they are yours always putting family first however you know you can one day you fall in love this love this love carries a virus this love infects you with this virus you now have to take this life and make everyday count realistically how would you go about doing that what would you do none of us have tomorrow promised to us i had to live through that in early when my wife died now that it is painfully obvious that tomorrow may not come i do my best to let my loved ones know that i love them to enjoy life and to not let small things pile up it isn't easy but it's better than stressing out or letting little things spoil good friendships Humphrey Bogart Virus Bon Jovi Procrastination Book of Isaiah EastEnders Code: Lyoko Please Save My Earth Jon Secada Great Teacher Onizuka Le Malade imaginaire About a Boy Pitaten Friends Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an Aerial (dance move) Antiviral drug Undergrads Singlish Extreme Programming Socrates Sheryl Crow Angel One (TNG episode) Days of our Lives Irna Phillips Colley Cibber HIV test Ex-gay Non-Hodgkin's lymphoma Haven (TNG episode) Cole Porter Marburg virus The Catcher in the Rye W.I.T.C.H. Yusuf al-Qaradawi Laura Schlessinger Search for Tomorrow The Star Wars Holiday Special Poker jargon Infantilism Sant Thakar Singh Virus classification Kimi Finster Dean Koontz The Adventures of Pete & Pete Babe Ruth's Called Shot Code 46 Girl (Destiny's Child song) The Marriage of Figaro AFI 100 Years series Jacob Good Times Melanie Thornton Cheese AIDS reappraisal Rabies Phoebe Buffay's songs Philip J. Fry Soap opera Poliomyelitis HIV The Rutles Drawn Together Charmed 1957 World Series One Tree Hill (TV series) Leslie Cheung Spanish flu Aphrodite Fleetwood Mac YuYu Hakusho Sly & the Family Stone Knife Cheating in poker Knots Landing